17
00:01:34,940 --> 00:01:36,940
[Second Chance Romance]

18
00:01:37,020 --> 00:01:39,940
[Episode 13]

19
00:01:41,790 --> 00:01:43,540
Do you think Zheng Yufan
can win an award?

20
00:01:44,950 --> 00:01:45,820
It seems unlikely.

21
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:47,570
I've seen her rehearse.

22
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:50,100
She's fallen at the same spot
several times.

23
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:51,540
It's been like this for days.

24
00:01:53,790 --> 00:01:55,540
Wasn't she doing well before?

25
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,820
Guess everyone has their limits.

26
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,660
Increasing the difficulty

27
00:02:01,710 --> 00:02:03,130
isn't necessarily a good thing.

28
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,410
Let's go.

29
00:02:06,710 --> 00:02:07,020
Go.

30
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,130
Ms. Zhuang,

31
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,170
I'm sorry.

32
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:22,850
I want to drop out.

33
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:24,850
Ms. Tan,

34
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:26,570
you had such high hopes for me.

35
00:02:27,150 --> 00:02:28,170
Sorry to disappoint you.

36
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:29,730
Yufan,

37
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,940
we all want what's best for you.

38
00:02:32,750 --> 00:02:34,380
If you think it's harder

39
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,820
because I changed the piece,

40
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:37,130
I hope you can trust me.

41
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,260
You can do this.

42
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:39,850
It's not about you.

43
00:02:40,190 --> 00:02:41,380
It's my own problem.

44
00:02:41,750 --> 00:02:42,380
Yufan,

45
00:02:42,630 --> 00:02:44,690
I know you're under a lot of pressure.

46
00:02:45,870 --> 00:02:47,170
But don't rush.

47
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,060
We can solve any problem together.

48
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:50,260
Don't try to talk me out of it,

49
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:50,730
Ms. Guan.

50
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:52,610
I've really made up my mind this time.

51
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,170
Thank you

52
00:02:54,190 --> 00:02:56,170
for all your care and support.

53
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,170
I've let you down.

54
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,060
Sorry.

55
00:02:59,710 --> 00:03:00,260
Yufan.

56
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:01,170
Ms. Guan.

57
00:03:01,630 --> 00:03:02,940
Don't go after her. Let her go.

58
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:03,820
But Ms. Zhuang,

59
00:03:04,310 --> 00:03:05,690
are we just letting her leave like this?

60
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,170
Yufan,

61
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:19,060
you dance so well.

62
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,290
Why are you quitting?

63
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:22,260
Do I dance well?

64
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:24,820
Qu Zhen,

65
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:26,500
you must keep dancing.

66
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,820
I hope to see you on stage someday.

67
00:03:30,190 --> 00:03:31,170
How nice.

68
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:33,940
Dancing makes you happy.

69
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:41,820
What's wrong?

70
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,570
You seem down.

71
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:45,260
No.

72
00:03:49,190 --> 00:03:50,170
Work issues?

73
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:13,690
Oh my.

74
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:16,820
Be careful.

75
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:17,250
Slow down.

76
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,170
It smells amazing.

77
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:25,050
This is such a feast.

78
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:27,290
I had hot pot with you a few times.

79
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:28,700
I basically got

80
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:29,370
all your favorites here.

81
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:32,050
Go wash your hands.

82
00:04:32,070 --> 00:04:33,610
Let's eat.

83
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:37,050
Tasty, right?

84
00:04:39,390 --> 00:04:40,810
You still need to eat properly.

85
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,050
There's nothing

86
00:04:42,070 --> 00:04:43,700
a hot pot meal can't fix.

87
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:45,290
When we were kids,

88
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:47,170
I loved watching you eat.

89
00:04:47,390 --> 00:04:48,460
Seeing you enjoy your food so much

90
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:49,930
always made me eat more too.

91
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,930
You've been talking
the whole time, hardly eating.

92
00:04:52,950 --> 00:04:53,700
Let me get some for you...

93
00:04:55,070 --> 00:04:55,930
Who is it?

94
00:04:56,950 --> 00:04:57,580
Who?

95
00:04:59,190 --> 00:04:59,930
Shuhan?

96
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:04,170
So you're here.

97
00:05:05,070 --> 00:05:06,930
I wondered who was having hot pot here.

98
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:08,170
I could smell it from outside.

99
00:05:08,190 --> 00:05:08,810
Here.

100
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:09,580
You didn't need to buy anything.

101
00:05:09,620 --> 00:05:10,580
Our place has everything.

102
00:05:12,180 --> 00:05:13,290
Our place?

103
00:05:13,510 --> 00:05:14,700
This is Tan Siting's place.

104
00:05:16,070 --> 00:05:17,170
Get her a seat.

105
00:05:17,190 --> 00:05:18,050
There's enough food.

106
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:19,460
Even if there wasn't, I'd still eat.

107
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,290
Sit here.

108
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:21,810
Don't sit so close to her.

109
00:05:21,830 --> 00:05:23,290
Might bump her foot later.

110
00:05:25,310 --> 00:05:25,700
Here.

111
00:05:26,070 --> 00:05:26,930
I haven't visited lately.

112
00:05:27,380 --> 00:05:27,930
How is

113
00:05:28,070 --> 00:05:28,580
your recovery?

114
00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:29,580
It's good.

115
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:31,050
Just following the doctor's orders.

116
00:05:31,620 --> 00:05:33,460
No discomfort now.

117
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:34,460
Just waiting to heal gradually.

118
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:37,170
Listen, a serious bone injury
needs a long time to heal.

119
00:05:37,190 --> 00:05:38,810
Make sure you're recovered
before going back to school.

120
00:05:38,830 --> 00:05:39,810
The school can wait.

121
00:05:40,830 --> 00:05:41,580
No.

122
00:05:41,740 --> 00:05:42,930
I still teach my students every day.

123
00:05:42,950 --> 00:05:43,460
You know what?

124
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:44,290
It's pretty funny now.

125
00:05:44,310 --> 00:05:45,930
I teach sitting in a chair

126
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:47,700
every day.

127
00:05:47,740 --> 00:05:49,290
It makes me feel like a professor.

128
00:05:49,830 --> 00:05:51,170
You are a professor.

129
00:05:51,830 --> 00:05:53,540
You know, a girl at our school

130
00:05:53,580 --> 00:05:53,930
asked,

131
00:05:55,190 --> 00:05:57,290
"What does Mr. Wang do for a living?"

132
00:05:58,070 --> 00:05:59,580
You know what I told her about Yuan?

133
00:05:59,620 --> 00:06:00,290
What did you say?

134
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,050
I said he's in homemaking services.

135
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:05,170
He does look the part.

136
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:06,580
Siting, let me tell you,

137
00:06:06,740 --> 00:06:08,460
my brother is like your brother.

138
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:09,930
If you need anything, just call him.

139
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:11,170
I know.

140
00:06:11,620 --> 00:06:12,580
He's like a brother to me.

141
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,340
Wang Zeyuan,

142
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,410
let me ask you something.

143
00:06:17,190 --> 00:06:18,020
If I

144
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:20,170
broke my leg one day,

145
00:06:21,430 --> 00:06:23,170
would you take care of me like this too?

146
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:24,810
You're overthinking it.

147
00:06:26,070 --> 00:06:28,290
Can we not talk
about such unlucky things?

148
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:29,700
But just to be clear,

149
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:30,930
if you really broke your leg,

150
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:31,810
I'd take care of you.

151
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,170
See?

152
00:06:34,510 --> 00:06:35,340
That's what sisters are for.

153
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:36,930
And we're siblings.

154
00:06:37,310 --> 00:06:37,930
You ungrateful brat.

155
00:06:39,830 --> 00:06:40,290
Where's the meat?

156
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,170
Don't take that piece of meat.

157
00:06:41,430 --> 00:06:41,810
It's overcooked.

158
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:43,050
I'll put in new ones for you.

159
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:44,460
I...

160
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:46,290
I can't eat this much anymore, Yuan.

161
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,780
I've definitely gained weight lately.

162
00:06:47,950 --> 00:06:49,580
Should I get some for you too?

163
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:51,930
Don't bother.
I don't accept pity offerings.

164
00:06:52,830 --> 00:06:53,930
But Tan Siting,

165
00:06:54,310 --> 00:06:54,930
you should watch out.

166
00:06:55,190 --> 00:06:56,290
You have gained a bit of weight.

167
00:06:56,310 --> 00:06:57,700
I noticed as soon as I walked in,

168
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:58,290
I'm telling you.

169
00:06:58,310 --> 00:06:59,340
She hasn't.

170
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:01,660
Don't overthink it.

171
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,580
I'm telling you,

172
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,410
after I recover,
I'll have gained weight for sure.

173
00:07:06,430 --> 00:07:07,170
Yuan, I...

174
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:10,540
I bet I won't even fit
into my dresses anymore.

175
00:07:11,190 --> 00:07:11,810
You look better with more weight.

176
00:07:12,190 --> 00:07:14,050
Stop brainwashing her, okay?

177
00:07:14,430 --> 00:07:15,540
She's a ballet dancer.

178
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,810
How can she dance if she gains weight?

179
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:18,050
Can she still do ballet
if she looks like me?

180
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:18,980
More like a bouncing bomb.

181
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:20,930
She could be the first.

182
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:22,930
Have a drink.

183
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:24,580
Can you drink?

184
00:07:25,830 --> 00:07:26,170
Cheers.

185
00:07:27,070 --> 00:07:27,290
Cheers.

186
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,170
To a speedy recovery.

187
00:07:33,950 --> 00:07:34,930
Look at you, so pathetic.

188
00:07:35,430 --> 00:07:36,290
I couldn't even drag you away.

189
00:07:39,950 --> 00:07:40,810
Are you available later?

190
00:07:42,190 --> 00:07:42,580
Why?

191
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:43,700
Nothing.
Have a couple of drinks with me.

192
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:45,050
I can keep you company.

193
00:07:45,510 --> 00:07:46,170
But I won't drink.

194
00:07:55,950 --> 00:07:56,290
Yuan,

195
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:57,440
have a drink with me.

196
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:02,880
If you want to talk

197
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,000
about Siting and me,

198
00:08:04,510 --> 00:08:05,270
don't bother.

199
00:08:05,950 --> 00:08:06,980
I'm not a minor.

200
00:08:07,510 --> 00:08:08,930
I'll take responsibility
for my own actions.

201
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:10,700
And

202
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:13,540
if Mom, Dad, or you

203
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:16,410
disagree because of what some relatives

204
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:17,700
or neighbors think,

205
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,850
then please tell them

206
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:21,810
that we live our lives for ourselves.

207
00:08:22,310 --> 00:08:23,780
Their idea of respectability

208
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:24,460
means nothing to me.

209
00:08:25,270 --> 00:08:26,810
You're pretty clever, huh.

210
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:30,050
You knew I called you here to talk.

211
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:33,060
But that's not what I wanted to discuss.

212
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:35,060
I want to tell you

213
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,940
that a relationship
is between two people.

214
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:38,060
My opinion

215
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:38,940
and our parents' opinions

216
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,180
don't matter.

217
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,490
Your own happiness is what matters.

218
00:08:44,510 --> 00:08:45,300
You don't believe me?

219
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,490
I know how you feel about Tan Siting.

220
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:51,940
And I know

221
00:08:52,390 --> 00:08:53,370
you've liked her

222
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,420
since you were very young.

223
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:56,060
Right?

224
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,060
I did start liking Siting
a long time ago.

225
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:03,300
I like her independence.

226
00:09:03,510 --> 00:09:04,370
I like her courage.

227
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:06,820
And I like how she gives her all

228
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,060
for her dreams.

229
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,060
Sometimes

230
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,940
I even feel like
I'm not good enough for her.

231
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,250
But other times

232
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,490
I feel we're quite alike.

233
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,420
Both are working hard

234
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,370
to create our own futures.

235
00:09:25,510 --> 00:09:26,700
I understand

236
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,100
everything you're saying.

237
00:09:29,790 --> 00:09:31,300
But let me ask you one thing.

238
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,060
Are you ready

239
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:34,820
to be a dad?

240
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,300
Tan Siting's child is alive.

241
00:09:43,270 --> 00:09:44,300
It's the child

242
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:47,300
we thought died twelve years ago.

243
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:48,820
He's alive.

244
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:50,770
Feng Rui raised him.

245
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:52,890
And Tan Siting

246
00:09:52,910 --> 00:09:55,340
went for a paternity test
a couple of days ago.

247
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:56,890
It is indeed her child

248
00:09:56,910 --> 00:09:58,770
from twelve years ago.

249
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,850
When she told me about this,

250
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:02,770
I was as shocked as you are.

251
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:04,890
It's really funny.

252
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,890
Like something out of a TV drama.

253
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,420
So, regardless of your relationship,

254
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:13,060
are you ready to be a dad?

255
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:14,890
I'll say it again.

256
00:10:15,390 --> 00:10:16,610
I don't care.

257
00:10:27,790 --> 00:10:28,250
Yuan,

258
00:10:29,390 --> 00:10:30,580
you're my brother.

259
00:10:31,150 --> 00:10:32,490
Siting is my good friend.

260
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:35,420
I hope you both can be happy.

261
00:10:36,550 --> 00:10:37,850
Anyway, I've told you now.

262
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,650
Be prepared.

263
00:11:09,260 --> 00:11:09,860
Class is over.

264
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:10,540
Stand up.

265
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:12,060
Good.

266
00:11:12,180 --> 00:11:13,260
Relax.

267
00:11:14,180 --> 00:11:14,700
Yes.

268
00:11:15,660 --> 00:11:16,460
Continue.

269
00:11:20,820 --> 00:11:21,580
Watch your expression.

270
00:11:22,420 --> 00:11:23,180
Good.

271
00:11:31,420 --> 00:11:33,020
Put feeling into your hands.

272
00:11:33,020 --> 00:11:33,900
Feet.

273
00:11:36,340 --> 00:11:37,820
Untightened. Good.

274
00:11:40,540 --> 00:11:41,140
Yes.

275
00:11:42,340 --> 00:11:43,340
Control.

276
00:11:44,380 --> 00:11:45,060
Go.

277
00:12:22,060 --> 00:12:23,220
I'm at Cabin Bar.

278
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:24,700
Got time? Come have a drink.

279
00:12:27,740 --> 00:12:29,300
♪Only your beautiful eyes
linger in my mind♪

280
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,250
I'm at Cabin Bar.

281
00:12:30,390 --> 00:12:31,610
Are you free? Come have a drink.

282
00:12:33,140 --> 00:12:37,340
♪Snowflakes fill the sky,
drifting midair♪

283
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:39,370
Are you free tonight?

284
00:12:39,510 --> 00:12:40,490
I'm at Cabin Bar.

285
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:41,370
Come have a drink.

286
00:12:43,020 --> 00:12:45,380
♪When you take my hand,
warmth begins to flow♪

287
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:47,010
Got time?

